      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, a cancelled flight, a classic tale of misfortune! Just like a mischievous goblin who loves to play tricks on unsuspecting travelers, your flight has decided to take an unexpected detour. But fear not, for even the most cunning goblin can't outsmart a determined traveler. Here are some goblin-inspired tips to help you navigate this unexpected journey:\n\n1. Check the airport's lost and found: Sometimes, a goblin might have misplaced your boarding pass, but it's usually found in the lost and found. It's like a treasure trove of misplaced goblin trinkets!\n\n2. Contact your airline: Speak to a friendly goblin (also known as a customer service representative) who can help you find alternative flights. They might have a secret passage (or flight) that you didn't know about.\n\n3. Look for connecting flights: Sometimes, a goblin might have a hidden passage (or connecting flight) that can take you closer to your destination. Keep an eye out for flights that might get you to Singapore faster.\n\n4. Consider a different airport: If you're feeling adventurous, you might want to consider flying out from a different airport. Just like a goblin might choose a different path to reach its goal,",
